The paper proposes a new approach to reinforcement learning that focuses on environment-specific information rather than invariant policies. This suggests that the paper is likely to be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves probing the environment, which suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) or systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that involve visual inputs, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
